  Ormat Industries  Ltd. dropped to the
lowest level in almost three months after the builder and
operator of geothermal plants said it expects to report a loss
for the fourth quarter and all 2010 after a writedown.  The shares fell 2.4 percent to 27.85 shekels, the lowest
since Nov. 28, at the 4:30 p.m. close in  Tel Aviv .  The Yavne, Israel-based company said there will be a
